Theo James' performance is particularly noted in Little White Lies' review. Knotfest uses the film's title metaphorically in "Monkey See, Monkey Kill." Vulture speculates on a potential "White Lotus" theory involving the monkey as the killer. RadioTimes analyzes the film's ending and explores its symbolism. name: Kash Patel
summary: The United States Senate has confirmed the appointment of Kash Patel as the next Director of the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI), despite concerns expressed by Democratic Senators. Patel, a loyalist to former President Donald Trump, has previously served as a top aide to the former President and as a top official at the Department of Defense. His confirmation has drawn criticism from some Democrats, who expressed concerns about his lack of experience in law enforcement and his potential to "carry out Trump's bidding" while leading the FBI. Despite these concerns, Patel was confirmed by a narrow vote in the Senate, with two Republicans joining all Democrats in opposition. Patel's family has roots in Gujarat, India, and his appointment has been met with mixed reactions in the United States and abroad.
